Euro-Area Retail Sales Rose 0.9% in June, Led by Germany

-- B y   S i m o n e   M e i e r
-- 
2011-08-03T09:09:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/euro-area-retail-sales-increased-0-9-in-june-led-by-germany.html
European retail sales rebounded in
June from a drop in the previous month, led by  Germany .  Sales in the 17-nation euro region grew 0.9 percent from
May, when they fell 1.3 percent, the European Union’s statistics
office in Luxembourg said today. Economists had projected a gain
of 0.5 percent, the median of 22 estimates in a Bloomberg News
survey showed. Sales fell 0.4 percent from a year ago.  In Germany,  Europe ’s largest economy, retail sales rose 6.3
percent from May, when they fell 2.5 percent, today’s report
showed. French sales advanced 0.7 percent, while Spanish sales
slipped 0.5 percent. In Ireland sales were flat, while in
Portugal they rose 0.9 percent. Both countries have received
European Union-led rescue funds.  The statistics office didn’t provide figures for  Greece ,
Italy and the Netherlands.  The euro extended gains after the data were released,
trading at $1.4317 at 11:08 a.m. in Brussels, up 0.8 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
